<br>
Seeing the Spiroc Lord is of most interest to warriors - I figured I'd stop by and ask you for your advice.<br>
<br>
My alliance is camped up on Horsey isle right now and we'll be logging on sometime this weekend to camp the lord for our warriors.<br>
<br>
I've read about 3 guides and countless posts on how this gets done but I wanted to check with you guys first before I send 30 people to their death (raid leader's favorite job btw).<br>
<br>
So...could you please confirm or add anything to the following?<br>
<br>
- Port in invis - Port in is safe - no one moves until everyone ports in.<br>
- Port in as at 6 o'clock, Guardian is at 3 o'clock, and recommended fighting area is around 8 o'clock (near some house?)<br>
- First pull will bring from 1-3 Vanquishers with all their pets in tow.  Paladin will pull (starting with the vanquisher with the pets lowest on the alphabet) DA then run back to the house(?)<br>
- Vanquishers go down first, followed by the lesser spirocs in alphabetical order, if guardian comes, kill him after you kill the vanquishers but before killing the lesser spirocs and he will respawn (immediately?) non aggro<br>
- If and when all the vanquishers and lesser spirocs go down and you have a *non* aggro guardian, it's time to pull the Spiroc Lord.  Spiroc lord goes down and then....(this is the part i need help with)<br>
+++ Does Sirran spawn when the Lord goes down?<br>
+++ If so we can't fight another lord until Sirran despawns or is trained away?  Or how do we pull another Spiroc Lord without aggro'ing sirran?<br>
+++ Will the Lord respawn immediately after he is killed so long as the guardian is still up and non aggro?<br>
+++ Will our camp at 8 o'clock be a decent place to operate this organized chaos?<br>
+++ In the event of a total party wipeout what are our options for CR?  Send the corpse summon team to horsey isle - port everyone back up - summon to horsey isle and try to break again?<br>
<br>
Seems this island is our only real challenge for the night...We're there for warrior blades and magician crowns so we're not really interested in the rest.  I just wanted to make sure that I had at least a somewhat solid strategy if I'm going to be sending countless people to their death.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance guys...<br>
<br>
